{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":760,"text":"With me here today"},{"time":2440,"text":"I brought something beautiful."},{"time":4920,"text":"This is a feather from one of the most\nbeautiful birds we have in Kenya,"},{"time":9600,"text":"the crested guinea fowl."},{"time":12600,"text":"But this feather is more than just that."},{"time":15560,"text":"If you've taken time when you are outdoors"},{"time":17840,"text":"to look at the feathers around you,"},{"time":19760,"text":"you'll have noticed"},{"time":21000,"text":"that there is this huge variety\nof different sizes,"},{"time":24760,"text":"shapes and even colors."},{"time":27840,"text":"The feather is one of the most\nastonishing pieces of technology"},{"time":32560,"text":"invented by the natural world,"},{"time":35120,"text":"and for centuries, this feather\nhas helped birds to keep dry,"},{"time":40160,"text":"to keep warm and even power flight."},{"time":44280,"text":"Only one section of the tree of life\ncan actually make a feather."},{"time":49400,"text":"Among all the world's animals,"},{"time":51360,"text":"birds are the only ones\nwho can make something"},{"time":53560,"text":"like what I'm holding today."},{"time":55960,"text":"I personally have given them a nickname,"},{"time":58360,"text":"and I like to call them the feathermakers."},{"time":62360,"text":"It is the major difference between birds\nand any other animals we have on earth,"},{"time":67840,"text":"and if you can't make a feather,\nyou cannot call yourself a bird."}]},{"cues":[{"time":71480,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":73720,"text":"For us humans, who are earthbound,"},{"time":76840,"text":"birds represent freedom."},{"time":79160,"text":"This feather has enabled birds\nto conquer gravity"},{"time":82680,"text":"and take to the air\nin an extraordinary way."},{"time":85760,"text":"Don't you sometimes wish\nyou could fly like a bird?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":90720,"text":"Birds are my passion,"},{"time":93320,"text":"and I want to change the way\neach one of you thinks about them."},{"time":97720,"text":"The easiest reason I love them so much\nis because they are beautiful."},{"time":102320,"text":"There are 10,000 species in the world,"},{"time":105640,"text":"and each one of them\nis uniquely beautiful."},{"time":110480,"text":"Birds are amazing,"},{"time":112480,"text":"and this talk is dedicated\nto all the birds of the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":116200,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":117800,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":121560,"text":"Indeed, these birds have been\npart of our lives and cultures"},{"time":126120,"text":"all over the world for centuries,"},{"time":128800,"text":"and every society has a story about birds."},{"time":131960,"text":"You probably have heard\nchildhood stories of different birds"},{"time":135680,"text":"and how they relate with man."},{"time":137680,"text":"I personally recently learned"},{"time":139520,"text":"that our human ancestors\nwould follow flocks of vultures"},{"time":143320,"text":"and then they would help them"},{"time":144760,"text":"to identify where carcasses\nhave been dropped by large carnivores,"},{"time":148240,"text":"and these humans will scavenge\nand eat part of that meat."},{"time":153960,"text":"Birds have been used as brands\nand labels all over the world."},{"time":157480,"text":"You know the bald eagle?"},{"time":158840,"text":"It was chosen as the national\nemblem for the US"},{"time":161640,"text":"because of its majestic strength,"},{"time":163800,"text":"beautiful looks"},{"time":165040,"text":"and even a long lifespan."},{"time":167520,"text":"And just like us humans"},{"time":169080,"text":"who have managed to live\nin virtually all habitats of this earth,"},{"time":173640,"text":"birds have also conquered the world."},{"time":177080,"text":"From birds such as\nthese beautiful penguins"},{"time":180040,"text":"that live in the cold ice caps"},{"time":182480,"text":"to even others like the larks,"},{"time":184560,"text":"who live in the hottest deserts\nyou can imagine."},{"time":187720,"text":"Indeed, these species\nhave conquered this world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":191320,"text":"Birds also build houses like us."},{"time":194000,"text":"The real pros in housebuilding"},{"time":196120,"text":"are a group of birds\nwe call the weaverbirds,"},{"time":199040,"text":"and this name they were given"},{"time":200480,"text":"because of the way\nin which they weave their nests."}]},{"cues":[{"time":203720,"text":"An interesting one:"},{"time":205320,"text":"birds also love and date\njust like us humans."},{"time":208720,"text":"In fact, you'll be surprised to know\nthat males dress to impress the women,"},{"time":214600,"text":"and I'll show you how."},{"time":216200,"text":"So here we have a long-tailed widowbird,"},{"time":218760,"text":"and this is how they would normally look."},{"time":221040,"text":"But when it comes to the breeding season,"},{"time":223480,"text":"everything changes,"},{"time":225800,"text":"and this is how he looks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":227800,"text":"(Audience murmurs)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":229120,"text":"Yeah?"},{"time":231320,"text":"Birds also, multiple species of them,"},{"time":235000,"text":"do love to touch and cuddle\njust like humans."},{"time":238600,"text":"And I know you're\nwondering about this one."},{"time":240920,"text":"Yes, they kiss too,"},{"time":243360,"text":"sometimes very deeply."}]},{"cues":[{"time":245080,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":248320,"text":"Some have even learned\nto cheat on their spouses."}]},{"cues":[{"time":250920,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":251960,"text":"For example, the African jacana:"},{"time":253960,"text":"the females will mate with multiple males"},{"time":256399,"text":"and then she takes off\nto find other males to mate with"},{"time":259360,"text":"and she leaves the male behind\nto take care of the chicks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":262560,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":264200,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":268120,"text":"And birds help us so much,"},{"time":270360,"text":"and they play very crucial roles\nin our ecosystems each day."},{"time":274640,"text":"Vultures clean up our environment"},{"time":276920,"text":"by literally digesting\ndisease-causing pathogens,"},{"time":280320,"text":"and they finish carcasses\nthat would otherwise cost us lots of money"},{"time":284200,"text":"to clear from the environment."},{"time":286120,"text":"A sizable flock of vultures\nis capable of bringing down a carcass"},{"time":290080,"text":"the size of a zebra straight to the bone"},{"time":292400,"text":"within just about 30 minutes."},{"time":295240,"text":"Owls help to rid\nthe environments of rodents"},{"time":298880,"text":"and this helps us a lot\nbecause it saves us money --"},{"time":301720,"text":"we don't lose our crops --"},{"time":303120,"text":"and secondly, we don't have\nto buy harmful chemicals"},{"time":306040,"text":"to handle these rodents."},{"time":309280,"text":"The beautiful sunbirds\nwe see in our environments"},{"time":312520,"text":"are part of nature's pollination crew,"},{"time":314960,"text":"and they help our plants to form fruits."},{"time":318320,"text":"Together with other\npollinators like insects,"},{"time":320920,"text":"they have actually helped us"},{"time":322480,"text":"to get most of the food crops\nthat we depend on for many years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":327920,"text":"Unfortunately, the story of birds\nis by far not perfect."},{"time":332520,"text":"They are faced by numerous challenges\nevery day wherever they live."},{"time":337160,"text":"Top on the threats facing birds"},{"time":338880,"text":"is habitat loss"},{"time":340360,"text":"and reduced food availability."},{"time":343440,"text":"Birds are also hunted,\nespecially migratory species"},{"time":346960,"text":"and ducks that congregate in water bodies."},{"time":350640,"text":"Poisoning is happening\nto flocks that like to stick together,"},{"time":354320,"text":"especially in places like rice schemes."},{"time":357720,"text":"Moreover, power lines\nare electrocuting birds"},{"time":361160,"text":"and wind farms are slicing birds"},{"time":363560,"text":"when they fly through the blades."},{"time":366320,"text":"Recently, we've heard the talk\nof climate change"},{"time":369360,"text":"making a lot of headlines,"},{"time":371200,"text":"and it's also affecting birds,"},{"time":373240,"text":"because birds are being forced to migrate\nto better breeding and feeding grounds"},{"time":377640,"text":"because unfortunately\nwhere they used to live"},{"time":379800,"text":"is no longer habitable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":382160,"text":"My own perspective\ntowards birds was changed"},{"time":384520,"text":"when I was a small boy in high school,"},{"time":386720,"text":"and there was this boy who struck,"},{"time":388400,"text":"injuring the wing and the leg\nof a bird we called the augur buzzard."},{"time":392480,"text":"I was standing there,"},{"time":394400,"text":"just a mere 14-year-old,"},{"time":396360,"text":"and I imagined a human being\nin a similar situation,"},{"time":399920,"text":"because this bird could not help itself."},{"time":402480,"text":"So even if I was hardly\nany biologist by then,"},{"time":406240,"text":"I gathered with three of my friends\nand we decided to house the bird"},{"time":410160,"text":"until it had regained strength\nand then let it free."},{"time":413680,"text":"Interestingly, it accepted\nto feed on beef from our school kitchen,"},{"time":418040,"text":"and we hunted termites around the compound\nfor its dinner every day."},{"time":422160,"text":"After a few days, it had regained strength"},{"time":424400,"text":"and we released it."},{"time":425680,"text":"We were so happy to see it flap its wings"},{"time":428240,"text":"and fly off gracefully."},{"time":430160,"text":"And that experience\nchanged the way we looked at birds."},{"time":434640,"text":"We went on to actually make a magazine,"},{"time":437640,"text":"and we called it the Hawk Magazine,"},{"time":439880,"text":"and this was in honor of this bird"},{"time":442000,"text":"that we had helped\nwithin our own high school."}]},{"cues":[{"time":445960,"text":"Those experiences in high school\nmade me the conservationist I am today."},{"time":451040,"text":"And a passion for birds\nshould especially matter for Africa"},{"time":454800,"text":"and all Africans,"},{"time":456280,"text":"because among all other continents,"},{"time":458600,"text":"Africa hosts some\nof the most amazing bird species"},{"time":461560,"text":"you can find anywhere in the world."},{"time":463840,"text":"Imagine having a name like \"shoebill.\""},{"time":466680,"text":"That's the name of that bird."},{"time":468680,"text":"And there are countries like DR Congo,"},{"time":472280,"text":"Tanzania, Uganda and Kenya"},{"time":474840,"text":"who are leading the continent\nin highest numbers of diversity"},{"time":478400,"text":"when it comes to the species."},{"time":481040,"text":"These birds continue\nto provide the continent"},{"time":483520,"text":"with very crucial ecosystem\nservices that Africa needs."},{"time":488000,"text":"Moreover, there is huge potential"},{"time":490880,"text":"for Africa to lead the world\nin avian tourism."},{"time":495480,"text":"The economy will definitely benefit."},{"time":498200,"text":"Imagine how many communities\nwill benefit from groups of tourists"},{"time":502440,"text":"visiting their villages\njust to see the endemic birds"},{"time":505640,"text":"that can only be found in those villages."}]},{"cues":[{"time":509320,"text":"How can we help birds together?"},{"time":511800,"text":"There is now a chance for all of you"},{"time":514960,"text":"to turn your passion for birds"},{"time":516799,"text":"into contributing\nto their continued survival,"},{"time":519720,"text":"and you can do that\nby becoming a citizen scientist."},{"time":524520,"text":"Citizen science is a growing trend\naround the world,"},{"time":528240,"text":"and we are having scenarios\nwhere people are sharing information"},{"time":531320,"text":"with the rest of the community\nabout traffic updates,"},{"time":534320,"text":"security alerts and so on."},{"time":536600,"text":"That is exactly what\nwe realized as bird-watchers,"},{"time":540400,"text":"and we thought, because birds\nare found everywhere,"},{"time":543480,"text":"if we've got all of you\nand everyone else in Africa"},{"time":546680,"text":"to tell us the birds\nthey find where they live,"},{"time":549080,"text":"where they school,\nor even where they work,"},{"time":551520,"text":"then we can be able to come up\nwith a map of every single species,"},{"time":556080,"text":"and from there scientists will be able"},{"time":558840,"text":"to actually prioritize\nconservation efforts"},{"time":561920,"text":"to those habitats that matter the most."}]},{"cues":[{"time":564400,"text":"Take for example these two projects,"},{"time":566480,"text":"the Africa Raptor DataBank,"},{"time":568280,"text":"which is mapping all birds of prey\nin the continent of Africa,"},{"time":572160,"text":"and the Kenya Bird Map,"},{"time":573480,"text":"which is mapping about 1,100 species\nthat occur in my country, Kenya."},{"time":578440,"text":"These two projects\nnow have online databases"},{"time":581440,"text":"that are allowing people to submit data,"},{"time":583920,"text":"and this is converted\ninto very interactive websites"},{"time":586920,"text":"that the public can consume\nand make decisions from."}]},{"cues":[{"time":590680,"text":"But when we started,\nthere was a big challenge."},{"time":592960,"text":"We received many complaints\nfrom bird-watchers,"},{"time":595440,"text":"and they will say,"},{"time":596720,"text":"\"I'm in a village,\nand I cannot access a computer."},{"time":599080,"text":"How do I tell you\nwhat birds live in my home,"},{"time":601720,"text":"or where I school, or where I work?\""},{"time":604120,"text":"So we were forced to renovate our strategy\nand come up with a sustainable solution."},{"time":609840,"text":"It was easy:"},{"time":611160,"text":"we immediately realized that mobile phones"},{"time":613400,"text":"were becoming increasingly\ncommon in Africa"},{"time":616080,"text":"and most of the regions\ncould get access to one."},{"time":619520,"text":"So we came up with\nmobile phone applications"},{"time":623240,"text":"that you can use on your iPhone\nand on your Android phone,"},{"time":626400,"text":"and we made them freely available"},{"time":628520,"text":"for every bird-watching\nenthusiast out there."},{"time":632800,"text":"So we came up with BirdLasser,\nwhich is used by the Kenya Bird Map,"},{"time":637080,"text":"and also we have\nthe African Raptor Observations,"},{"time":640800,"text":"which is now used\nby the African Raptor DataBank."},{"time":643880,"text":"This was a huge breakthrough in our work"},{"time":646040,"text":"and it made us get\nenormous amounts of data"},{"time":648760,"text":"from every birder\nout there in the regions."},{"time":652400,"text":"With this, we realized\nthat citizen science"},{"time":654800,"text":"is indeed very powerful,"},{"time":656880,"text":"the reason being,\ncitizen science is adaptive."},{"time":660920,"text":"And we were able to actually\nconvert many bird-watchers"},{"time":664400,"text":"to start sharing new information with us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":670240,"text":"When we were starting,"},{"time":671480,"text":"we didn't know that birds\ncould be a huge gateway"},{"time":674080,"text":"to approaching conservation\nof other forms of animals."},{"time":677600,"text":"Interestingly, now\nin the Virtual Museum for Africa,"},{"time":680880,"text":"we have maps for dragonflies\nand damselflies,"},{"time":684080,"text":"butterflies and moths,"},{"time":685840,"text":"reptiles, frogs, orchids, spiders,"},{"time":690000,"text":"scorpions, and yes,\nwe are even mapping mushrooms."},{"time":693880,"text":"Who could have imagined mapping mushrooms?"},{"time":696560,"text":"So this showed us that indeed\nwe've created a community of people"},{"time":701160,"text":"who care about nature in Africa."}]},{"cues":[{"time":704720,"text":"I hereby call upon all of you"},{"time":706960,"text":"to join me in promoting the value of birds"},{"time":710200,"text":"within your communities."},{"time":712000,"text":"Please just tell your friends about birds,"},{"time":714680,"text":"for we are always inclined\nto love and care for that which we know."},{"time":719720,"text":"Please spend a few minutes\nin your free time"},{"time":722000,"text":"when you are at work,\nat school, or maybe at home,"},{"time":725120,"text":"to at least look around you\nand see which beautiful birds are there."},{"time":728720,"text":"Come join us in citizen science"},{"time":730840,"text":"and tell us the birds you're finding\nin the places where you visit."},{"time":734840,"text":"Even simpler,"},{"time":736160,"text":"you could buy your child or your sibling"},{"time":738800,"text":"a pair of binoculars"},{"time":740640,"text":"or a bird book"},{"time":742000,"text":"and let them just appreciate\nhow beautiful these birds are."},{"time":745520,"text":"Because maybe one day\nthey will want to care"},{"time":748400,"text":"for that one which they know and love."}]},{"cues":[{"time":751320,"text":"The children indeed are our future."},{"time":754120,"text":"Let us please teach them\nto love our feathermakers,"},{"time":757640,"text":"because the love of birds"},{"time":759600,"text":"can be a huge gateway\nto appreciating all forms of nature."}]},{"cues":[{"time":763960,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":765200,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":770480,"text":"Thank you."}]}]}